reviews.text: Good food!
服務同態度勁差。以前有食開。麻辣湯地 差左 頭一年好香麻香越食越無。豬扒 炸到干 十分粗口。連食物都唔好食。未必會再去
不禮貌係巴蜀軒多年來的賣點！明明有枱永遠要5 個人迫住一張坐！味道無前幾年香，現在辣得無層次，因缺少了當初麻完再辣快感，肉質也好粗糙，可能要買平料，現在比較適合低要求口味人仕去食！
每次去到，都會直接說：「雞扒麻辣四川粉小辣凍檸茶走甜」。

reviews.text: Very tasty noodle in Causeway Bay. Highly recommend the pork chop noodle, in particular for those spice-savvy. Very spicy, hot and exciting and yet yummy. The quality  maintains the same over the years, not deteriorated.
Back after 3 months and found it is not as spicy for the same item i am ordering
Good porkchop spicy noodle

Ordered the recommended pork chop and single bone chicken wing on sore spicy soup noodle.  It is very salty. The preserved salty sore vege is really salty. It makes the soup very salty. The pork chop is heavily salted  with cumin, though a typical north western Chinese style, it tastes very strong. 

Not for those who couldn't bear strong tastes. 

The recommended drink 桂花圓肉菊花茶 is not my recommendation. Maybe my tongue was destroyed by the salty noodle already.

No service even in terms of local noodle shop standard.  Can't say the staff is friendly.  One even turned on the speaker of his mobile  to watch video.  Guess he is the boss or relative to the boss.

Taste spicy soup and noodle, but the side dish just ok.
And the restaurant is so packed, you will not enjoy seating there for long.  
And sometimes they will ask you go to the back of the restaurant, which basically is a backstreet with cover, messy and dirty

reviews.text: Very tasty noodle in Causeway Bay. Highly recommend the pork chop noodle, in particular for those spice-savvy. Very spicy, hot and exciting and yet yummy. The quality  maintains the same over the years, not deteriorated.
小小的一間米線餐廳，差不多一定要搭台。有很多款式既餸可以搭配，亦有特有既四川粉。不過水準一般。
辣得地道，辣得過隱。只是堂食時較擠逼!
